  "prompt": "Is there such a thing as an agnostic theist?",
  "response": "Yes, there is such a thing as an agnostic theist. An agnostic theist is someone who believes in the existence of a deity or deities but also holds that the existence of such a being is ultimately unknown or unknowable. In other words, they may have faith in a higher power but acknowledge that they cannot have definitive knowledge or certainty about the nature of that being or the specifics of its existence.\n\nThis position can be seen as a middle ground between atheism (the lack of belief in deities) and theism (the belief in deities). Agnostic theists might engage in spiritual practices or embrace religious traditions while remaining open to the possibility that their understanding of God or the divine is limited or incomplete.",
